US President Donald Trump will appoint luxury handbag designer Lana Marks as the new ambassador to South Africa. A statement from the Whitehouse read: Trump caused a stir back in August when he asked his secretary of state, Mike Pompeo, to study the seizure and expropriation of land in South Africa, along with the killing of farmers. Trump posted a note on Twitter, alleging the South African government was “seizing land from white farmers”.  The South African government called Trump’s tweet “misinformed”. Read: Trump misleads again with claim of South Africa farm murders